Label: trapezoid
Definition: Both OPS and IPS quadratic to rectangular or oblong in planar view, with at least the two longer faces (sides) parallel, and with straight, convex, or oblique ends. IPS usually smaller, resulting in trapezoidal cross sections, and typically not strongly faceted or ornamented.
Synonym 2: Festucoid Class: Rectangular, Oblong 1b,g, in part
Synonym 3: Double outline (IIIA3, in part, III B1-4), Trapezoids: Non-sinuous (V, in part)
